---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="The Story | Jamal Williams">
	<section class="space-y-12 py-20 animate-fade-in">
		<header class="space-y-4">
			<a href="/" class="text-slate-500 hover:text-white transition-colors flex items-center gap-2 mb-8">
				<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M15 19l-7-7 7-7" /></svg>
				Back Home
			</a>
			<h1 class="text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white sm:text-7xl font-display animate-slide-up">
				Jamal <span class="text-gradient">3.0</span>
			</h1>
			<p class="text-xl text-slate-400 max-w-2xl animate-slide-up" style="animation-delay: 0.1s;">
				From Tech Support at 15 to Digital Architecture and Soulful Photography.
			</p>
		</header>

		<div class="glass p-8 md:p-12 rounded-3xl space-y-8 text-slate-300 leading-relaxed animate-slide-up" style="animation-delay: 0.2s;">
			<div class="space-y-6">
				<p>
					I help brands tell their stories because storytelling is in my blood. I grew up in a family that documented every moment—not just the snapshots, but the lore surrounding them.
				</p>
				<p>
					My technical journey started early. At 15, I quit my paper route and got my first "real" job doing tech support for Compuserve. I haven't worked a job that wasn't computer-related since. From Oklahoma State to Dell in Austin, I spent over two decades building large-scale enterprise systems.
				</p>
				<p>
					But in 2010, the spark caught flame. I rediscovered what my parents always knew: a photo's true power lies in the story it tells. My journey evolved from taking photos to understanding how visuals connect people to narratives.
				</p>
			</div>

			<div class="bg-slate-900/80 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 space-y-4">
				<h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white font-display">The Transition</h3>
				<p class="text-sm text-slate-400">
					In January 2025, a layoff served as a catalyst. It was the push I needed to move from corporate stability toward <strong>entrepreneurship and creative freedom</strong>. 
				</p>
				<p class="text-sm text-slate-400">
					Now based in Detroit, I've returned to leadership as an Engineering Manager while concurrently building the foundations of my own creative practices.
				</p>
			</div>

			<p>
				Today, I merge technical expertise with artistic vision. Whether I’m guiding software teams or helping professionals build their brand, I understand the critical importance of a clear, impactful message supported by great visuals.
			</p>
		</div>

		<footer class="pt-8 flex justify-center">
			<a href="/stack" class="btn-secondary">The Sovereign Stack →</a>
		</footer>
	</section>
</Layout>
